## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="032e8-104">Provedores separadas são hospedados por um aplicativo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="032e8-104">Decoupled providers are hosted by an application.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="032e8-105">Dois métodos podem ser usados pelo aplicativo para criar instâncias de classes WMI disponíveis: publicar/revogado ou o método de retorno de chamada.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="032e8-105">Two methods can be used by the application to make instances of WMI classes available: publish/revoke or the callback method.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="032e8-106">Usa o método de retorno de chamada de <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.InstrumentationManager.RegisterType%2A> e <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.InstrumentationManager.UnregisterType%2A> métodos.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="032e8-106">The callback method uses the <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.InstrumentationManager.RegisterType%2A> and <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.InstrumentationManager.UnregisterType%2A> methods.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="032e8-107">No modelo de publicação/revoke, a infra-estrutura WMI fornece o comportamento padrão para muitos dos métodos que você precisa escrever você mesmo no método de retorno de chamada.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="032e8-107">In the publish/revoke model, the WMI infrastructure provides default behavior for many of the methods you have to write yourself in the callback method.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="032e8-108">Isso inclui a enumeração e associar os métodos.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="032e8-108">These include the enumeration and bind methods.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="032e8-109">Nesse modelo, o aplicativo cria instâncias e publique.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="032e8-109">In this model, the application creates instances and publishes them.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="032e8-110">O aplicativo é responsável por garantir que as propriedades de chave das classes são respeitadas.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="032e8-110">The application is responsible for ensuring that the key properties of the classes are respected.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="032e8-111">O aplicativo também é responsável por excluir instâncias.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="032e8-111">The application is also responsible for deleting instances.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="032e8-112">No modelo de retorno de chamada, a infra-estrutura WMI espera que o aplicativo tenha métodos que lidam com a enumeração, associação e quaisquer outros métodos necessários para implementar a funcionalidade do provedor.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="032e8-112">In the callback model, the WMI infrastructure expects the application to have methods that handle enumeration, binding and any other methods required to implement the functionality of the provider.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="032e8-113">Ele chama o aplicativo para essa funcionalidade e falhará se ele não existe ou não está implementado corretamente.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="032e8-113">It calls into the application for this functionality and fails if it does not exist or is not implemented properly.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="032e8-114">O aplicativo registra o tipo de suas classes WMI com a infraestrutura chamando <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.InstrumentationManager.RegisterType%2A> e indica que ele não quer mais as classes WMI expostas por meio da chamada <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.InstrumentationManager.UnregisterType%2A>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="032e8-114">The application registers the type of its WMI classes with the infrastructure by calling <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.InstrumentationManager.RegisterType%2A> and indicates that it no longer wants the WMI classes exposed by calling <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.InstrumentationManager.UnregisterType%2A>.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="032e8-115">O exemplo a seguir demonstra como usar o modelo de publicação/revoke.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="032e8-115">The following example demonstrates how to use the publish/revoke model.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="032e8-116">Duas instâncias da classe roteador são criadas e publicadas.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="032e8-116">Two instances of the router class are created and published.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="032e8-117">Eles são revogados mais tarde.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="032e8-117">They are later revoked.</span></span>  
  
```  
public class Sample_InstanceProvider  
{  
public int Main (string[] args)   
{  
Router r_one = new Router ();  
r_one.Name = "one";  
InstrumentationManager.Publish(r_one);  
Router r_two = new Router ();  
r_two.Name = "two";  
InstrumentationManager.Publish(r_two);  
// ....  
InstrumentationManager.Revoke(r_one);  
InstrumentationManager.Revoke(r_two);  
return 0;  
}  
}  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="032e8-118">No exemplo a seguir, o método de retorno de chamada de registro é usado para expor a classe RouterNew.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="032e8-118">In the next example, the callback method of registration is used to expose the RouterNew class.</span></span>  
  
```  
public int MainNew(string[] args)   
{  
    InstrumentationManager.RegisterType(typeof(RouterNew));  
    // ....  
    InstrumentationManager.UnRegisterType(typeof(RouterNew));  
    return 0;  
}  
```

  
  
## Examples  
  
```  
static int Main(string[] args)  
{  
   InstrumentationManager.RegisterType(typeof(MySampleProvider));  
   return 0;  
}  
